race.comment: Very competitive race to finish with quite a few winning chances. VINTAGE STAR (6) has won five of 16 including two at this track and distance. He draws low and he gets a 3kg claim, both of which can aid his chances here. Suspect he will be in the finish. Punters have had a love-hate relationship with STREETCAR FURY (8) but he did the job last start and might be able to go on with it now. He loves Murray Bridge but the big track at headquarters also looks suitable. FREE BEER (3) has a knack of ending up in the last race and he's become a pin-up horse for punters. He is flying and can win again with luck. ROUND TWO (10) can do a bit wrong but there is enough ability there to feature.
